Robert Walker disappeared yesterday at around 18:30. His family says he was busy cooking and wanted to go to a café quickly. He left the food on the stove and the gate open, planning to return soon but hasn’t been seen or heard from since.  He was wearing a blue overall and black T-shirt underneath and was driving a silver Mazda BT 50 double cab with a canopy.
Vehicle registration: MP 114480. A photo of the vehicle he had left in. A missing persons case was filed with the police and the family is appealing to the public to help search for him in the Hendrina/Middelburg area. Anyone with any information on his whereabouts can contact Elize Visagie at 072 390 6665.